<p>Hurricane Melissa struck Jamaica on Oct. 28 as an exceptionally powerful storm, making landfall there at Category 5 strength with sustained winds reported near 185 mph and producing life‑threatening storm surge and flooding . The system knocked large parts of Jamaica offline and severely damaged homes and infrastructure, then weakened while crossing the Caribbean and hit eastern Cuba as a major hurricane while Cuban authorities evacuated hundreds of thousands in advance . Forecasters warned of extreme flash flooding and landslides across the eastern Caribbean and the Bahamas as Melissa continued its track .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/69B6ROcRy6Z8Ey_JjCjqiaePz-MRVg9_0dK_EbigzQIF4AVjhkHY4ISX60YaiABRDfVDpMQY7INgqIHDH9O2-mtPoQs2w7lpwdzBLA0p67sFeg6BtmJvoZqopEmC4J_HfzXpLmbSGSTLjHU2yZqkxd5Lu0LfmeRroFO-g5gbYQESRvQbDP-QXNpCwRW8WIWRqe5BB_q-EDjZJZLx6t9CRyshiesmqba1MYcsWZ6SCb_QskixNtZj3x7OelCblwsXzxVNMwn-kB2TABqG9g' alt='A man walks under the rain before the arrival of Hurricane Melissa in Canizo, Santiago de Cuba, Oct. 28, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Reported casualties: Early reports list at least seven deaths after Jamaica was hit, and officials have declared disaster zones while damage assessments continue</li><li>Communications blackout: Most of Jamaica experienced widespread internet and telephone outages and major airports were temporarily closed, hampering early damage surveys and relief coordination</li><li>Power and shelter needs: Electricity companies reported outages affecting a large share of customers and nearly 6,000 people moved into temporary shelters as authorities search for water, power and medical access</li><li>Regional threat: Meteorologists warned Melissa posed extreme flood and landslide risk to Haiti, the Dominican Republic, Cuba and the Bahamas as it moved northwestward</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Jamaica government: Government officials declared disaster areas and appealed for rapid damage assessments and outside assistance as power and communications were cut in many parishes. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/29/jamaica-declares-disaster-after-monstrous-melissa-ravages-island'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Cuban government: Authorities ordered large-scale evacuations and moved more than 700,000 people to safer areas ahead of Melissa&#x27;s landfall to reduce loss of life. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/climate/2025-10-29/hurricane-melissa-makes-landfall-in-cuba-with-winds-of-up-to-125-miles-per-hour.html'>El Pais</a>)</li><li>United States National Hurricane Center: Forecasters emphasised the continuing danger of life‑threatening storm surge, flash flooding and destructive winds as Melissa tracked across the Caribbean. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/hurricane-melissa-cuba-landfall-jamaica/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>World Meteorological Organization (WMO): Meteorological authorities and scientists noted Melissa&#x27;s unusual strength and flagged the storm as an extreme event for the region. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/climate/2025-10-29/melissa-a-textbook-hurricane-in-times-of-climate-crisis.html'>El Pais</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/cp8yz2jgk0go'>Strong winds and flying debris as Hurricane Melissa makes landfall</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/b495b10f-220f-4d27-96f5-9242df7f9d24'>Hurricane Melissa hits Cuba after striking Jamaica with violent wind and rain</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/hurricane-melissa-to-batter-jamaica-as-the-island%27s-strongest-storm-on-record-in-almost-2-centuries'>Category 5 Hurricane Melissa brings flooding and catastrophic winds to Jamaica</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/live/2025/10/29/weather/hurricane-melissa-cuba-jamaica'>Live Updates: Hurricane Melissa Makes Landfall in Cuba After Lashing Jamaica</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://english.elpais.com/climate/2